sentence: Since it's your first time with us, I'm going to ask you some questions so we can proceed with your appointment.
What about your date of birth?
Who can contact in case of any emergency?
May I ask the reason for your appointment?
I had an accident for couple weeks ago and now I have been feeling some dizziness and strong headaches.
Any injuries on your neck or back area?
No, not that I can feel.
Do you have any type of diabetes?
Have you had any type of cancer?
Do you have any circulation or heart problems?
Do you take any medicine daily?
Do you have high blood pressure?
It's minor, I don't even take pills.
Thank you David. Please have a seat and I will talk to you in a minute.
